e:  state: PA  headline: Winter Weather Advisory until TUE 1:00 PM EST  county_fips:  category: Met  url:  urgency: Expected  severity: Moderate  certainty: Likely  geographicname: Lehigh County  state_name: Pennsylvania      69 News reporter Priscilla Liguori caught up with wrestler Darian Cruz ahead of his trip to the Olympics in Paris.  BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Fans of a former Bethlehem Catholic and Lehigh University standout are again invited to a local pub to watch the wrestler compete at the Olympics in Paris.  A watch party is scheduled to start Friday at 12:30 p.m. at Sotto Santi Pizzeria Pub in south Bethlehem to cheer on Darian Cruz.  Cruz, representing his grandparents' native Puerto Rico, is scheduled to wrestle Aman Sehrawat of India around 1:15 p.m. for the bronze medal in the 57 kg division.  69 News was live early Thursday morning as fans gathered at the restaurant at 5 a.m. to watch Cruz in his opening bouts. He got a pin during round one then fell in the quarterfinals 12-2 to top seed at 57 kg, Rei Higuchi. Higuchi of Japan later advanced to the finals, set for Friday, which means Cruz is still alive and now has a shot at bronze.  Cruz won two PIAA Class 2A individual wrestling titles at Becahi in 2012 and 2013 and a NCAA Division I national title at Lehigh University in 2017.  Head Wrestling Coach at University of Pennsylvania Roger Reina announced the addition of Olympian Darian Cruz as an assistant coach on Thursday afternoon.      Get local Breaking News alerts sent directly to your inbox.  Success!An email has been sent towith a link to confirm list signup.  Error!There was an error processing your request.  Watch all of WFMZ-TV News and Syndicated Programing 24/7 on your Streaming App enabled TV.  Your browser is out of date and potentially vulnerable to security risks.We recommend switching to one of the following browsers:  Get up-to-the-minute news sent straight to your device.\"}"